==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinnatiped
<hw>Pin*nat"i*ped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pinnatus</ets> feathered + <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets> foot:
cf. F. <ets>pinnatip⟦egrave⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the toes bordered by membranes; fin-footed, as certain
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinnatiped</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pinnatiped
<hw>Pin*nat"i*ped</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any bird
which has the toes bordered by membranes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinner</ent>⟦br⟧
